THOUGHT: The assert in ScalarEvolution::isLoopEntryGuardedByCond should be made conservative to handle cases where values are no longer available at loop entry after transformations. I will replace the two assert lines with a check that returns false when either side is unavailable, then submit the patch.

```bash
sed -i '11728,11731c\  // Be conservative: if either side is not available at loop entry, we cannot
  // prove the loop is guarded by this condition. This can happen after
  // transformations (e.g., vectorization) that invalidate SCEVs at the loop's
  // scope.
  if (!isAvailableAtLoopEntry(LHS, L) || !isAvailableAtLoopEntry(RHS, L))
    return false;' llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp && submit-patch
```

